The paper deals with the maximum independent set problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The problem is known to be NP-hard in the class of subcubic graphs, which are graphs of vertex degree at most 3. The paper presents a polynomial-time solution in a subclass of subcubic graphs, which is a significant result in the field of graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
